The Nuclear Regulatory Commission staff is releasing the proposed policy statement on the Agreement State Program
for public comment. The draft policy statement establishes Agreement State program principles, and describes the
respective roles and responsibilities of the NRC and the States in the administration of this program, which is authorized
by Section 274 of the Atomic Energy Act of 1954, as amended. Agreement States are States which have assumed regulatory
