a hearing on the issue. If the State does not request a hearing, the Commission will make a final decision on the issue.
If the State does request a hearing, the Commission will initiate the hearing process described below. 

The hearing for the termination [including the termination of a program that had been previously suspended] of an
Agreement State program will be an informal hearing conducted either by the Commission itself, or at the Commission's
discretion, by a Special Agreement State Board appointed by the Commission. In cases where the Commission determines
that a Special Board will be used, the Board will consists of three members: (1) the chair of the Organization of Agreement
